args: The fools in this castle are far\ntoo soft for their own good!
Dragons have no place in this world,\nso why does everyone keep trying\nto protect them?!
I'm going to find that prince and make him\ntell me the weakness of the beasts!

OW! H-hey! Wh-who goes there?!
Don't you know it's dangerous to suddenly
cut across an open corridor like that?!
I could have been killed!
If I study these younglings, I might finally\nlearn the weakness of dragons!
Muah ha ha! Now just hold still\nwhile I capture you, wee ones...
You fool dragons shouldn't be walking\nabout LETTING me catch you...
Yes? What? What is it?\nAre you trying to say something?
Hrmm. Well, all right then.\nLet me go prepare some food.
...Behold! I have made you both some of\nmy special soup!
What are you saying? I'll admit the color\nisn't very appetizing, but it tastes divine,\nI assure you.
It is rare that the Child of Miracles\nprepares a meal for someone.\nLet alone dragons!
Goodness, they ate everything!\n...Well then? What did you think?
I'm going to take that as a positive\nanswer. ...Hmm? What now?

Well, they're turning in circles and seem
to have their legs crossed, sooo...
ACK! You can't possibly be planning
to relieve yourselves HERE!
Whew! Made it just in time.
Right then, what's with that yawn?\nAre you ready for an afternoon nap?
Well, if you want to sleep, do so.\nNo good comes from fighting the urge.
Ah, I know. I will grant you the honor of\nhearing me sing a lullaby.
Sleeping child, happy child...\nLet the good sleep take you...\nAnd awful dreams not wake you...
Well, that worked wonders.\nLet's hope they have a good nap.
...Amane? Wait, is that Fydon and Felyx?!
Er, I'm sorry. Did you put them to bed?
I apologize for the trouble my dragons\ncaused you, but thank you for taking\nsuch good care of them.
You should indeed be thanking me!
Those two were wandering aimlessly\nbefore I took them under my wing.
But don't think this will happen again.\nIt was a once-in-a-lifetime honor!
You're a fine mother for one so young.
And do not think to forget it, good sir.\nWait, are you treating me like a child?!
I am 24 years old, and a woman grown!
Amane! You're going to wake them!
They really are very troublesome children.\nWell, I'd best get back to my...
Wait, what WAS I doing before I started\ndragonsitting those two, anyway?
Ah, yes!! I remember! I was on my way to\nspeak with {player_name}!
This is no time to be watching them sleep.\nI have work to do!
You will tell me the weakness of dragons,\n{player_name}!
Er, did she just say she wanted to know\nthe weakness of dragons?
Heh. The truth was right in front of her,\nand yet she missed it somehow.
Some dragons simply have a weakness\nfor people who are kind.
